about.summary: Creates dummy columns from columns that have categorical variables (character or factor types). You can also specify which columns to make dummies out of, or which columns to ignore. Also creates dummy rows from character, factor, and Date columns. This package provides a significant speed increase from creating dummy variables through model.matrix().

name: r-fastdummies
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.6.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-fastdummies
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/fastDummies_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/fastDummies/fastDummies_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 27131adf025fb7d2b63cca7d99b1ac9ab2ee51e26ffeefd8dd4b71a872fe17ef

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table
    - r-tibble
    - r-stringi
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table
    - r-tibble
    - r-stringi

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('fastDummies')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('fastDummies')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/jacobkap/fastDummies
  license: MIT
  summary: Creates dummy columns from columns that have categorical variables (character or factor types). You can also specify which columns to make dummies out
    of, or which columns to ignore. Also creates dummy rows from character, factor, and Date columns. This package provides a significant speed increase from creating
    dummy variables through model.matrix().
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - uday1889
